description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;University Hospitals Plymouth NHS Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Post Title Locum Consultant Breast Radiologist &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Grade Locum Consultant&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract Fixed Term &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please apply via NHS Jobs.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;University Hospitals Plymouth NHS Trust (Derriford Hospital, Plymouth) invites applications for a Locum Consultant Breast Radiologist post available until the end of June 2021. The post is 10 sessions full time, 9 clinical (DCC) session and one supporting (SPA) session. There is no on-call commitment. The successful applicant would join a team of 4 consultant breast radiologists and a consultant breast radiographer delivering a symptomatic and screening radiology service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The unit is modern and energetic, purpose built and well organised. The main role would be to work in symptomatic one-stop clinics, breast assessment clinics, to film read for the NHS Breast Screening Programme (must have a proven track record of doing this), localisation, MDT presentation, with the option to assist in reading Breast MRI studies. We are an active teaching department with radiology registrars frequently moving through the department, and advanced practitioners training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Empathy and sensitivity, good communication skills, team-working and a cheerful and positive ethos is required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details please contact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Jim Steel, Consultant Radiologist/Service Line Director 01752 431883&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Undergraduate Medical Education&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Plymouth University Peninsular School of Medicine and Dentistry (PUPSMD) has been praised by the GMC for its innovative approach to undergraduate medical education. The curriculum is based around problem based learning and has been highly ranked by our graduates in how they felt prepared for postgraduate medicine. Your role will include important opportunities to engage with undergraduate education, in both the hospital environment and the school itself, to continue this vital job of producing tomorrow’s doctors and allied health care professionals&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
